I got a call my from my endocrine oncology surgeon last week that I was dreading. 

For 7 years I’ve had cancerous lymph nodes in my neck that we’ve been regularly monitoring to make sure they didn’t grow. 
Last week my surgeon to tell me that unfortunately the lymph nodes have doubled in size and I needed surgery asap to remove them. 

Tomorrow I head in for what I hope is my very last cancer surgery. They will have to make a 10 inch incision in my neck so my recovery will be long and painful. 

It sucks, I don’t want to do it, but I’m so ready to get it done and be on the other side!! 

Thank you to all of you who have followed my cancer journey all of these years. Apparently we aren’t quite done 🙂 I hope you’ll keep walking with me to get this last bit of cancer completely out!!
 #amandasarmy 
#thyroidcancer #cancersucks #cancer

I’m pretty sore and tired, but the surgery went well and my surgeon was able to take out all of the lymph nodes! 

Now the recovery begins.

Thank you all so much for all of your prayers and for reaching out. I so appreciate it❤️
I got out of the house and went on a VERY slow walk today. I think it’s going to take me a couple of hours to recover, but it was worth it 🙂

Headed for our first night out since my surgery! Recovering has been going well. I still have a lot of stiffness and some pain, but I’m so thankful it’s done and I’m on the mend!! 
#thyroidcancer #cancersurvivor

Please pray for these sweet babies and families. My heart is absolutely breaking as I start to hear who has been lost. 
It’s awful and unimaginable.

We had an incredible Easter! We loved getting to celebrate another year with the cutest little bunny 🥰🥰🥰

“He is Risen, just as He said!”
 
HAPPY EASTER EVERYONE!!!

In 5 days my cousin Kristy goes in for her second brain surgery. 
She hasn’t been able to fully work since February and they have to travel several hours every time she sees her doctor.
To say they have a lot going on right now is a major understatement.
I definitely know what it’s like to have one thing after another happen and what feels like non-stop set backs. 
Would you join me in helping to relieve some of their financial burden if you’re able? 
Either way, let’s cover them in so much prayer and get her back to her two beautiful boys!!! Find the link in my profile. 
❤️❤️🙌🏻❤️❤️🙌🏻

Happy Fathers Day @reidpatterson. We love you so much and we are so glad we get to celebrate you!! 
We started the day with Reid letting me sleep in and then making breakfast…..classic Reid :) 
🥰🥰🥰#fathersday

We officially have a Preschool Graduate!! 
Adalyn has been in some sort of daycare since she was 3 months old. She has made so many adorable little friends and has learned so much. I know we’ll blink and she’ll graduate from High School, so we are celebrating every moment of now. Next stop, KINDERGARTEN!!

She’s officially in KINDERGARTEN!!! 
I can’t even believe it. 
She ran right into school, sat in her seat and just said “Bye Mom, see you later!”

I’m both so proud of her and so sad at the same time. My baby is growing into an amazing, independent, fabulous little girl. 
#backtoschool #kindergarten

I did a thing!!! I’ve been looking for a journal for a long time that I can do for 5 minutes a day and asks me simple prompt questions every morning and every night. 
I couldn’t find what I was looking for…..so I made my own and I LOVE IT!! 
I made it available on Amazon for anyone who might be looking for the same 🥰🥰🥰 (link is in my bio)

After seeing me write in my Journal every day, Adalyn asked if I would create one for her too. SO I DID! I created a boy and girl version and I love them! I made it a bit more simple with space to draw pictures if your child can’t quite write yet. 
Links to all 3 journals are in my profile (or check my stories:) 
#journal #kidsjournal

I made an Advent Journal! I noticed for myself that I would get through the Holidays and didn’t feel like I sat and contemplated the past year. I know Christmas is overwhelming, so I decided to design an Advent journal with prompt questions that walk you through each week of Advent. 
I hope this year we can all end stronger and go into the New Year with a renewed sense of self. 
Check out the link in my profile to get your copy!

Oh Hello FORTY!!!! ❤️🎉🥳🎊🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻

Aging is a privilege. Society tells us to do everything we can to prevent it, but with each new grey hair and wrinkle comes the thankfulness of life! 

 When I was diagnosed with cancer 10 years ago, I didn’t know if I’d live to see this day…..but here I am, reminding myself and everyone else that it is a privilege to age. 
So bring it on 40! I can’t wait to see what you have in store 🥰
